<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1784,2027]" lastBlockId="23.[189,1399,267,330]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[189,450,1784,1810]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="289 - 292" refId="ref262885" refString="Happold M. 2013 d. Rousettus aegyptiacus Egyptian Rousette. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 289 - 292. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="d">Happold (2013d: 290)</bibRefCitation>
distinguishes four African subspecies in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[935,1108,1785,1810]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Rousettus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis box="[935,1108,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">R. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which 
<emphasis box="[1234,1314,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">leachii</emphasis>
occurs from NE 
<collectingCountry box="[299,359,1820,1846]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">DRC</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[395,494,1820,1846]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
and southwards to 
<collectingCountry box="[720,872,1820,1846]" name="South Africa" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, as well as on the islands of 
<collectingRegion box="[1200,1283,1820,1846]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Pemba" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Pemba</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1398,1820,1846]" name="Tanzania" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
and Mafia. A second subspecies, 
<emphasis box="[568,667,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">unicolor</emphasis>
(Gray, 1870), occurs from 
<collectingCountry box="[979,1072,1856,1882]" name="Senegal" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Senegal</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1107,1232,1856,1882]" name="Cameroon" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, Bioko Island, and southwards to 
<collectingCountry box="[410,500,1892,1918]" name="Angola" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Angola</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergmans" box="[511,761,1892,1919]" firstAuthor="Bergmans" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="79 - 126" refId="ref257439" refString="Bergmans W. 1994. Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 4. The genus Rousettus Gray, 1821. Beaufortia 44 (4): 79 - 126. Available from http: // www. repository. naturalis. nl / document / 548564 [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="journal article" year="1994">Bergmans (1994: 91)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that in 
<emphasis box="[963,1043,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">leachii</emphasis>
, a weaker skull and dentition, as compared to the typical subspecies, justifies the separation as a subspecies, but he also indicates that the variation within 
<emphasis box="[479,559,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">leachii</emphasis>
is very large and that it would be worth examining a larger series from over its entire distribution area. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman &amp; Hill" box="[563,875,2001,2027]" firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref265812" refString="Hayman R. W. &amp; Hill J. E. 1971. Order Chiroptera. In: Meester J. &amp; Setzer H. W. (eds) The Mammals of Africa, an Identification Manual. Part 2. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington." type="book" year="1971">Hayman &amp; Hill (1971: 12)</bibRefCitation>
furthermore mention that the morphological and geographic limits of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[491,631,268,293]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Rousettus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis box="[491,631,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[692,772,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">leachii</emphasis>
are not yet clear, and intergrading may occur in the equatorial zone.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860101" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860101/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[189,232,1930,1956]" targetBox="[233,1353,307,1878]" targetPageId="22">
